A '''mobile community''' is a group of people generally united by shared interests or goals who interact:
* considering their context (e.g. time, space, social), * by means of location-independent information technology, * and also including mobile access to existing community infrastructures.<ref>Rannenberg, Kai, Denis Royer, and André Deuker, eds. "The future of identity in the information society: Challenges and opportunities." Springer Science & Business Media, 2009.</ref>
